	(1019,45,'title',''),
	(1020,45,'_title','field_602657cc293e7'),
	(1021,45,'content_ml_rich_text_english','[Pseudonym] told Amnesty International that she spoke with a friend who said that she had been raped repeatedly by camp guards.\r\n<blockquote>“I was terrified when I found out that I would be sent to a facility, because my neighbour, who was in her twenties, was a camp, and she and I had a drink and she shared her secrets. She said she was raped and forced to have an abortion … She told me that she said several Han people raped her, that ‘2 held my hands 2 held my leg and one raped me’.”</blockquote>\r\nThere have been several reports of rape and other forms of sexual violence among women formerly detained in the camps. Many formerly detained women say they have been subjected to sexual degradation, including being filmed in the shower or ordered to apply chili paste on their genitals. Others describe younger women disappearing overnight with police officers only to reappear the following day, in pain, without explanation. There are also some accounts of rapes, both of women and men, sometimes with electric batons inserted into the vagina or anus. Some witnesses report police officers informally admitting to raping women and girls in the camps.  Gang rapes are allegedly perpetrated by officers in front of other detainees, who are forced to witness the abuse.'),
